 volume explores the credibility of media and communications as a construct, ranging from the foundations of media history to the consequences of current debates for journalistic practice. Its contributions analyze structural factors and motives behind trust in media and media skepticism, in addition to discussing the strategic realignment of research efforts in communication studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aGlaubwürdigkeit. 4aInformationsqualität. 4aMedienkritik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aCredibility.  aInformation Quality.  aMedia Criticism.1 aAverbeck-Lietz, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAverbeck-Lietz, Stefanie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlome, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlome, Astrid, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlöbaum, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöning, Holger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEberwein, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEberwein, Tobias, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGranow, Viola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackob, Nikolaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarren, Otfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuhnhenn, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyen, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Henrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuiring, Oliver, econtribut